Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createBusNetGroup(25.10)                              createBusNetGroup(25.10)

Name
       createBusNetGroup - Creates a net group for buses

Syntax
       createBusNetGroup

       [-help]

       [-considerClone]

       [-createBusSinkGroup]

       [-dontCommit]

       [-file <string>]

       [-ignoreBusSize <integer>]

       [-ignoreConnectivity]

       [-ignoreMultiPartitionPinNet]

       [-netGroupOptionsList <string>]

       [-overwrite]

       [-prefix <string>]

       [-reverseOrder]

       [-useShortName]

       [-bus <string> | -all ]

       [-forTopOnly | -forPartitionOnly ]

       [-includeMacro | -forPartitionOnly ]

       [-checkOnly | {[-bus <string>] [-all ]} ]

       Creates a net group for buses.

Parameters
       -all   Creates  a  net  group connected to the design partition for all
              the buses.

              Note: This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -bus parame-
              ter.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -bus <string>
              Creates a net group connected to  different  partitions  of  the
              specified bus only.

              Note: This parameter is mutually exclusive with the -all parame-
              ter.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -checkOnly
              Checks and reports all the buses present in the design.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -considerClone
              Creates a net group for buses connected to clones.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -createBusSinkGroup
              Creates BusSinkGroup instead of a net group.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -dontCommit
              Creates  nets  groups  and  stores the info in a file instead of
              creating in the DB.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -file <string>
              Specifies the name of the file in which the defined  groups  are
              stored.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -forPartitionOnly
              Specifies  that the net groups should be connected to partitions
              only.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -forTopOnly
              Specifies that the net groups should be  connected  to  the  Top
              only.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each createBusNetGroup parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man createBusNetGroup

       -ignoreBusSize <integer>
              Specifies that the buses smaller than the specified size  should
              be ignored.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -ignoreConnectivity
              Specifies  that the partition connectivity should be ignored and
              the net groups should be created for the whole bus.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -ignoreMultiPartitionPinNet
              Specifies that the buses connected to multiple partitions/clones
              should be ignored.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -includeMacro
              Specifies that bus net group being created should have a connec-
              tion with macros.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -netGroupOptionsList <string>
              Specifies attributes (like optimizeOrder, spread etc.) that  can
              be added to the bus net group.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -overwrite
              Overwrites the already created net group be deleting the current
              net group element from an earlier association.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -prefix <string>
              Specifies a prefix for the bus net group.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -reverseOrder
              When  specified,  the bus order of the buses in the net group is
              reversed.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -useShortName
              When specified, a short name is applied to the bus net group.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Related Information
              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

